      "p": [
        {
          "text": "We’re pleased to invite you to the opening reception of Tianyue Zhong’s second solo exhibition with the gallery. UNTIL brings together three large-scale oil pai",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 265,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 190
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
          "fontSize": "21.76px",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fontStyle": "normal",
          "lineHeight": "27.2px",
          "letterSpacing": "normal",
          "textTransform": "none",
          "color": "rgb(0, 0, 0)",
          "backgroundColor": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)",
          "textAlign": "start",
          "margin": "0px",
          "padding": "0px 0px 27.2px"
        },
        {
          "text": "The three paintings in UNTIL emerge from a single originating moment Tianyue Zhong experienced during a visit to the Tashi Lhunpo Monastery in Shigatse, Tibet (",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 456,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 354
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
          "fontSize": "21.76px",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fontStyle": "normal",
          "lineHeight": "27.2px",
          "letterSpacing": "normal",
          "textTransform": "none",
          "color": "rgb(0, 0, 0)",
          "backgroundColor": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)",
          "textAlign": "start",
          "margin": "0px",
          "padding": "0px 0px 27.2px"
        },
        {
          "text": "Zhong revisited this experience through collage and, subsequently, through painting. Rather than reconstructing a fixed scene, she worked to re-enter the sensat",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 809,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 245
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
          "fontSize": "21.76px",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fontStyle": "normal",
          "lineHeight": "27.2px",
          "letterSpacing": "normal",
          "textTransform": "none",
          "color": "rgb(0, 0, 0)",
          "backgroundColor": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)",
          "textAlign": "start",
          "margin": "0px",
          "padding": "0px 0px 27.2px"
        },
        {
          "text": "Recurrence and repetition play a central role in this process, not to reinforce narrative but to dissolve it. By revisiting the same imagery time and again, Zho",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 1054,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 272
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
          "fontSize": "21.76px",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fontStyle": "normal",
          "lineHeight": "27.2px",
          "letterSpacing": "normal",
          "textTransform": "none",
          "color": "rgb(0, 0, 0)",
          "backgroundColor": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)",
          "textAlign": "start",
          "margin": "0px",
          "padding": "0px 0px 27.2px"
        },
        {
          "text": "While each painting maintains its own internal logic, they remain closely linked. In Walking Bare, the composition radiates outward from the lower edge, where t",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 1326,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 299
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
          "fontSize": "21.76px",
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fontStyle": "normal",
          "lineHeight": "27.2px",
          "letterSpacing": "normal",
          "textTransform": "none",
          "color": "rgb(0, 0, 0)",
          "backgroundColor": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)",
          "textAlign": "start",
          "margin": "0px",
          "padding": "0px 0px 27.2px"
        },
        {
          "text": "Throughout her practice, Zhong moves between observation and painting, allowing these processes to inform one another. What emerges is a visual language rooted ",
          "rect": {
            "x": 640,
            "y": 1625,
            "w": 599,
            "h": 163
          },
          "fontFamily": "\"Unica77 LL\", Helvetica, sans-serif",
